# PostgreSQL Password Template
#
# This is an EXAMPLE file. Copy to psql_password and edit.
#
# Generate a strong password:
#   openssl rand -base64 32
#
# OR use a password manager to generate 32+ character password
#
# Steps:
#   1. cp psql_password.example psql_password
#   2. Edit psql_password with a real strong password
#   3. chmod 600 psql_password
#   4. Never commit psql_password to Git (it's in .gitignore)
#
# Password requirements:
#   - Minimum 32 characters
#   - Mix of letters, numbers, special characters
#   - No dictionary words
#   - Unique (not reused elsewhere)
#
# Example strong password (DO NOT USE THIS!):
# Kx8mP2vN9qR4sT7wY3zA5bC6dE8fG1hJ0

CHANGE-ME-TO-A-STRONG-PASSWORD-32-CHARS-MINIMUM
